The article is a statement by the President on the House of Representatives' passage of PAYGO legislation. The President commends the House for their support of fiscal discipline and emphasizes the need for new initiatives and tax cuts to be paid for. He states that passing today's costs onto future generations must stop and that PAYGO was instrumental in moving from deficit to surplus in the 1990s. The President expresses gratitude to various individuals and groups for their support and urges the Senate to approve PAYGO so that he can sign the bill into law.